<TITLE> bdnews24.com correspondent receives media award </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 28 (bdnews24.com) -- The Comprehensive Disaster Management Project has selected bdnews24.com correspondent Moinul Hoque Chowdhury for its Media Award in Disaster Management for 2007, an official from the organisation said Thursday. Moinul said: "This award was initiated by the government and will encourage people in journalism." "Such initiatives in a disaster-prone country like Bangladesh will reinforce mass awareness in disaster management," the young reporter said. Dhaka University graduate Moinul started his career as a DU correspondent and worked for Ajker Kagoj and Inquilab, among other media houses, before moving to bdnews24.com. The CDMP selected five reporters in all for the awards. "Moinul Hoque Chowdhury was selected for his five chapter report entitled 'Climate change and vulnerable Bangladesh'," CDMP official MS Morshed told bdnews24.com. "The ministry of disaster management introduced the award in 2006, and this year's winners will receive their awards in the second week of March," Morshed said. The other four award-winners are: Nikhil Bhadra of the daily Sangbad, The New Age's Comilla correspondent Yasmeen Rima, Imdad Sikder of the daily Jahan and Ahmed Pipul from NTV. The daily Sangbad's Nikhil Bhadra told bdnews24.com that journalists provide an service that increases public awareness on important issues. bdnews2
